# Playwright Conventions

- Use `data-testid` attributes for selectors — never rely on CSS classes or DOM structure
- Prefer `getByRole`, `getByText`, `getByTestId` over raw CSS selectors
- Use `expect(locator).toBeVisible()` before interacting with elements
- Always use `test.describe` to group related scenarios
- Use Page Object Model for pages visited by more than one test file
- Avoid hard-coded waits — use `waitForSelector`, `waitForResponse`, or auto-retrying assertions

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
await page.click(".btn-primary.submit-form");
await page.waitForTimeout(3000);
expect(await page.$(".success-msg")).toBeTruthy();

// ✅ GOOD
await page.getByTestId("submit-button").click();
await expect(page.getByRole("alert")).toHaveText("Saved successfully");
```
